cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.NE

This paper is about enhancing neural machine translation (NMT) with pre-specified translations. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which deals with natural language processing and computational linguistics. The paper also involves machine learning techniques, which suggests that it could belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper proposes a data augmentation method, which could fall under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also mentions using image captioning as an example, which could relate to cs.CV (Computer Vision). Finally, the paper involves improving translation fidelity, which could be related to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
